        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Order-of-accuracy tests on canonical benchmark problems (lid-driven cavity, rotating pipe flow) must demonstrate observed order within 10% of theoretical order for all relevant discretization schemes. Achieved: observed order 1.92 vs. theoretical 2.0 for second-order upwind; within tolerance."
      },
      "rationale": "Code verification was performed using the method of manufactured solutions and canonical benchmark problems. Observed spatial order of accuracy (1.92) is within 10% of the theoretical second-order value, confirming correct implementation of the discretization scheme for the hemolysis-relevant flow regime."
