      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the regulatory-standard QoI per FDA guidance on hemolysis testing. Its mechanistic link to plasma-free hemoglobin elevation and clinical hemolysis endpoints is well-established in the literature. The QoI is directly relevant to the COU decision."
